The paper proposes a framework for improving the action exploration of policy gradient DRL algorithms in high-dimensional continuous action spaces, specifically in challenging high-dimensional motor tasks involving articulated agents. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), computer vision (cs.CV), and systems and control (cs.SY).
